It was already non-terminal, blame @YaelDillies. :-) I'll clean it up.
Ugh. It results in a 6 line `simp only`.
Is the idea that it's better to merge now and sort this out later?
Yes, Joachim will fix this but he's travelling at the moment. We need to keep `nightly-testing` compiling every day or we lose the ability to test Lean PRs against Mathlib.
This is not essential. I'm just trying to make `negSucc` less visible / more quickly dealt with by `simp`. It's still an unsatisfactory work-in-progress.
Not thrilled by this regression. The hypothesis `hn` after `norm_cast` is now `hn : False ∧ n = 0`
